Japanese Boxer Defends Orient Pacific Title
TOKYO , November 19 ( Xinhua ) -- Japan 's Hisashi Teraji defended his Orient-Pacific light heavyweight boxing title in Osaka on Thursday .
Teraji knocked down Wallace , the Orient-Pacific ninth-ranked contender , in the first round with a right straight to the face .
But Wallace took it to the 12th and final round .
Teraji was making his third defense of the title he won from Garth Cussion of Australia in Japan in April 1996 .
